***WASHINGTON, D.C.’S LARGEST CHOCOLATE CELEBRATION***
1)February 8th (Saturday)-“2nd Annual Champagne et Chocolat 
Black-Tie Valentine's Celebration at the French Embassy”
Sponsored by Baci Chocolates and the French International Culinary 
Society LA MAISON FRANCAISE, Embassy of France, 4101 Reservoir Rd. 
N.W., WDC, $95, tax and tip inclusive, 7-9:30 PM-Reception Style with 
Chocolate Desserts, Hand-Made Chocolates, Champagnes and Country 
Buffet and from 9:30-11:30 PM is Dancing to a Live Band and 
Chocolate Fondues and More Champagne! Dress is Black Tie suggested.

IF YOU LOVE CHOCOLATE (AND CHAMPAGNE) THIS EVENT IS FOR YOU!

-Live Chocolate Sculpting by Notter Intl. School of Confectionary

-5 or More of D.C.’s Top Pastry Chefs Creating Hand-Made Desserts,
***Current Pastry Chef Commitments***
(1)Equinox Restaurant,
(2)Cake Love – the Infamous Warren Brown!

-Baci Chocolates and Other Gourmet Sweets and Confections,
-Chocolate Fondues and Full French Country Buffet
-Dancing and Joie de Vivre to Live Music Provided by Night and Day
-Champagne Flowing Until the End!
Please Note: this is a standing/reception style event with limited
seating.
Tickets at https://secure.tasteusa.com/cgi-bin/order/order.cgi?X_DC
or call 202-333-5588 ($5 Surcharge)
