MAKE YOUR RESERVATIONS NOW!
2)Your Invitation to Inspiration in 2003
Washington DC Restaurant Week Jan 13 - 19
Honor that New Year's resolution to eat better and treat 
yourself well. Join more than 80 of Washington, DC's finest 
restaurants for awe-inspiring, multi-course meals prepared 
especially for this gourmet event. Lunch is just $20.03 and 
dinner is $30.03.  The Washington, DC Convention and Tourism 
Corporation and the Restaurant Association Metropolitan Washington 
are proud to present the fourth Washington, DC Restaurant Week 
from January 13 - 19, 2003.
Click here for a listing of participating restaurants 
http://www.washington.org/restaurantwk/
||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||| 

3)The Fifth Annual Fine Art of Cuisine at the Ritz Carlton, 
Tysons Corner, Virginia includes many great events:
“A Winter Night with Michel Richard and Champagne Taittinger”
on Friday, January 17th, $175/person,
Total Wine and More Grand Wine Tasting and Culinary Market place
Salon I and II, 11:30 a.m.- 4 p.m., $60/person,
sample nearly 250 wines from more than 100 wineries on
Saturday, January 18, and the “Chef’s Salute Dinner Honoring
Dennis Cakebread and Gary Danko” is the same night, $150/person,
and “An Artists’ Fare Brunch” $60/person is on Sunday, January 19th.
Participate in wine seminars, cooking demonstrations, and book signings.
The Culinary Marketplace will highlight some of the leaders in the
industry with regards to food products, kitchenware and restaurants.
There are 14 seminars included in the Grand Wine Tasting.
These seminars are reserved on a first come basis and seating will be 
available 15 minutes prior to the scheduled seminar time.
Tickets will be distributed on January 18 at the registration table 
located in The Ballroom Foyer. A ticket is required for entrance 
to the seminar.  Call 703-917-6505 to purchase tickets.
